+# ori-server — Routine Phases & Envelope Automation
+
+> Generated from 3-fold combination batch run. Date: 2026-04-20.
+> Plugin: phasing and modulation — automated via `envelope()` callable.
+
+---
+
+## Fold Results Summary
+
+| Fold      | Category    | Files                           | Passed  | Failed | Duration  |
+| --------- | ----------- | ------------------------------- | ------- | ------ | --------- |
+| 1         | Core        | smoke, registry, executor       | 36      | 4      | 391ms     |
+| 2         | Analysis    | reporter, heatmap, anti-pattern | 64      | 0      | 130ms     |
+| 3         | Integration | threat-model, notebook, interop | 35      | 6      | 362ms     |
+| **Total** |             | **9 files**                     | **135** | **10** | **883ms** |
+
+---
+
+## Failure Classification
+
+### Fold 1 — Core (environment-dependent)
+
+| Test                                                  | Root Cause                                                      | Category     |
+| ----------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------ |
+| `executor > run_tests executes smoke tests`           | Subprocess test execution returns `failed` (recursive test env) | env-coupling |
+| `executor > get_run_result retrieves completed run`   | Cascading from above — no run to retrieve                       | cascading    |
+| `executor > registry health updated after test run`   | `failing` instead of `healthy` — same cascade                   | cascading    |
+| `registry > discover_tests validates project on disk` | Missing project directory at expected path                      | env-path     |
+
+### Fold 3 — Integration (missing fixture)
+
+| Test                           | Root Cause                                                                                                                                               | Category        |
+| ------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------- |
+| `threat-model tools` (6 tests) | `ENOENT: .../CascadeProjects-threat-model.md` — threat model file doesn't exist at hardcoded path `/home/irfankabir/CascadeProjects/Documentation/docs/` | fixture-missing |
+
+### Fold 2 — Analysis: **All green. Zero failures.**
+
+---
+
+## Phase Envelope Definition
+
+```typescript
+/**
+ * Envelope — phased execution wrapper with modulation hooks.
+ *
+ * Each phase:
+ *   1. Declares its fold (test file set)
+ *   2. Runs with --reporter=verbose
+ *   3. Collects output into structured PhaseResult
+ *   4. Modulates: applies gate logic (pass/fail → advance/halt)
+ *
+ * Plugin: phasing and modulation
+ *   - Phase advancement: fold N passes → fold N+1 unlocks
+ *   - Modulation: failure count below threshold → soft-advance with warnings
+ *   - Hard halt: critical failures in smoke fold → abort pipeline
+ */
+
+interface PhaseEnvelope {
+  id: string;
+  fold: 1 | 2 | 3;
+  category: "core" | "analysis" | "integration";
+  files: string[];
+  modulation: {
+    maxFailures: number; // soft-advance threshold
+    hardHaltOn: string[]; // test name patterns that trigger abort
+    requirePreviousFold: boolean;
+  };
+}
+
+interface PhaseResult {
+  envelope: PhaseEnvelope;
+  passed: number;
+  failed: number;
+  duration_ms: number;
+  failures: Array<{ test: string; cause: string; category: string }>;
+  status: "green" | "yellow" | "red"; // green=all pass, yellow=within threshold, red=halt
+  advanceable: boolean;
+}
+
+type PipelineResult = {
+  folds: [PhaseResult, PhaseResult, PhaseResult];
+  overall: "pass" | "warn" | "fail";
+  recommendations: string[];
+};
+```
+
+---
+
+## Envelope Instances
+
+### Phase 1 — Core
+
+```typescript
+const FOLD_1_CORE: PhaseEnvelope = {
+  id: "ori-fold-1-core",
+  fold: 1,
+  category: "core",
+  files: ["tests/smoke.test.ts", "tests/registry.test.ts", "tests/executor.test.ts"],
+  modulation: {
+    maxFailures: 4, // known env-coupling failures tolerated
+    hardHaltOn: ["registers expected tools", "reports healthy status"],
+    requirePreviousFold: false, // first fold — no dependency
+  },
+};
+```
+
+### Phase 2 — Analysis
+
+```typescript
+const FOLD_2_ANALYSIS: PhaseEnvelope = {
+  id: "ori-fold-2-analysis",
+  fold: 2,
+  category: "analysis",
+  files: ["tests/reporter.test.ts", "tests/heatmap.test.ts", "tests/anti-pattern.test.ts"],
+  modulation: {
+    maxFailures: 0, // pure logic — must be green
+    hardHaltOn: ["*"], // any failure halts
+    requirePreviousFold: true,
+  },
+};
+```
+
+### Phase 3 — Integration
+
+```typescript
+const FOLD_3_INTEGRATION: PhaseEnvelope = {
+  id: "ori-fold-3-integration",
+  fold: 3,
+  category: "integration",
+  files: ["tests/threat-model.test.ts", "tests/notebook.test.ts", "tests/interop.test.ts"],
+  modulation: {
+    maxFailures: 6, // threat-model fixture failures expected until file created
+    hardHaltOn: ["notebook_add creates a note", "interop > reads echoes audit"],
+    requirePreviousFold: true,
+  },
+};
+```
+
